<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n41188d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41188d">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41188d"> 188(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ES shows girl / her angel in a / mirror</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"> <font color="green">[<font size="-1">PERSONAL CHARACTERISTICS</font>]</font> The pretty maiden, only fifteen or sixteen years old, had often asked &lsquo;Uncle&rsquo; Swedenborg to show her a spirit or an angel. At last he consented, and leading her to a summer-house in his garden, he palced her before a curtain that had been lowered, and then said. &ldquo;Now you shall <mark>see an angel</mark>&rdquo;; and as he spoke, he drew up the curtain, when the maiden beheld <mark>herself reflected in a mirror</mark>.&rdquo; <small> George Trobridge, <a name="GTLS" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#GTLS"><cite title="source">A Life of Emanuel Swedenborg</cite></a>, 2nd ed. (??) 305 [312]</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
